{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TimeZoneProtocol"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"text":"PointerWrapper","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTimeZone"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is refcounted and immutable."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Each time zone has an identifier (for example, ‘Europe\/London’) which is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"platform dependent. See [ctor"},{"code":"GLib.TimeZone.new","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] for information on the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"identifier formats. The identifier of a time zone can be retrieved using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GLib.TimeZone.get_identifier","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A time zone contains a number of intervals. Each interval has an abbreviation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to describe it (for example, ‘PDT’), an offset to UTC and a flag indicating"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"if the daylight savings time is in effect during that interval. A time zone","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"always has at least one interval — interval 0. Note that interval abbreviations"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are not the same as time zone identifiers (apart from ‘UTC’), and cannot be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"passed to [ctor","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.TimeZone.new"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Every UTC time is contained within exactly one interval, but a given","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"local time may be contained within zero, one or two intervals (due to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"incontinuities associated with daylight savings time).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"An interval may refer to a specific period of time (eg: the duration","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"of daylight savings time during 2010) or it may refer to many periods","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"of time that share the same properties (eg: all periods of daylight","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"savings time).  It is also possible (usually for political reasons)"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that some properties (like the abbreviation) change between intervals","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"without other properties changing.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTimeZone"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Alternatively, use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef"},{"text":" as a lighweight, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTimeZone"},{"text":" represents a time zone, at no particular point in time.","type":"text"}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TimeZoneProtocol"}],"symbolKind":"protocol","roleHeading":"Protocol","title":"TimeZoneProtocol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TimeZoneProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib16TimeZoneProtocolP","role":"symbol"},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","type":"inheritsFrom","title":"Inherits From","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"]},{"title":"Conforming Types","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZone","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneRef"],"type":"conformingTypes","kind":"relationships"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol\/identifier","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol\/time_zone_ptr-osvz"]},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol\/adjustTime(type:time:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol\/findInterval(type:time:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol\/getAbbreviation(interval:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol\/getIDentifier()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol\/getOffset(interval:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeZoneProtocol\/isDst(in